						<summary>

						<p>On pillar No. 8 of the Pātāḷa-Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Dated <hi rend="italic">Pramādin, Āshāḍha</hi> śu. • • • • (in late characters). (Cyclic year wrongly read as <hi rend="italic">Virōdhin</hi> in A.R. 1956-57).</p>						

						<p>Enjoins the temple-servants, not to touch the god without taking a bath, and the worshippers, not to leave their foot-wear in the temple in front of god Kēśavarāya lest they go to hell.</p>						

						</summary>
